title: Computational morphology and morphogenesis for empowering soft-matter engineering
description: Morphing soft matter, which is capable of changing its shape and function in response to stimuli, has wide-ranging applications in robotics, medicine and biology. Here, we highlight advances and challenges in developing computational techniques, and explore the potential applications enabled by such models.
